  "description": "Bird was silent. \u00a0no obvious behavior. \u00a0not eating, or apparently hunting for food, although there were probably 25 American Robins, \u00a0and many Cedar Waxwings whose major intent was to get a drink of water and eat Russian Olives. \u00a0Was he doing the same thing? \u00a0I didn't see him do either. \u00a0Only one bird. \u00a0Juvie. \u00a0Was ID's by folks at What's this bird when I submitted pictures to their FB page. \u00a0It is a life bird for me. \u00a0I, Jill Smith, was with a friend, Dottie Russell, who also saw the bird but didnt get pictures, nor could she ID it.",
